<li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">The Spine is an organ of locomotion and posture maintenance. The spine consists of 33 vertebrae (bones). There are cushion-like structures called discs between each of the vertebra that act as shock absorbers and helps in flexibility and movement in the spine. Each disc is made up of a tire-like outer band called the annulus fibrosus and a gel-like fluid inner substance called the nucleus pulposus.</li>
<li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">Together, the vertebrae and the discs provide a protective tunnel (the spinal canal) to house the spinal cord and spinal nerves. These nerves run down the center of the vertebrae and exit to various parts of the body. When the disc or cushion slips into the spinal canal causing compression of the nerve then its called Slip Disc OR HERNIATED DISC or Spinal Stenosis. Compression of nerve results in Back Pain OR Buttock pain or LEG PAIN OR back pain traveling down the leg and patients complains of pain in leg with numbness and difficulty in walking. this pain is also called Sciatica</li>
