									<ul>
<li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">A herniated disc may cause various symptoms and does not have similar complaints in all patients. The symptoms include include dull or sharp pain in back , Low Back Pain , Back Pain , muscle spasm, Locked back , stiffness in back , Morning stiffness , Leg pain , Numbness in calf or, Pain in back travelling down to legs with numbness and weakness, tingling, or referred pain to leg commonly referred as sciatica . Bulging disc or a Herniated disc can cause similar symptoms as extruded or ruptured disc. Usually, just one leg is affected.</li>
<li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">If you have a herniated disc in your neck (cervical spine), you may have referred pain down your arm and into your hand. Leg and arm pain caused by a herniated disc is also called radiculopathy.</li>
<li><img src="img/founder_li_icon.png" class="wow flipInX animated animated" data-wow-iteration="infinite" alt="pic" style="visibility: visible; animation-iteration-count: infinite; animation-name: flipInX;">Although rare but Herniated disc or slip disc loss of bowel or bladder control called cauda equina syndrome and rarely can cause paralysis – weakness of one or both lower limbs. The weakness of foot due to nerve compression is called foot drop and needs surgery at earliest for recovery. These conditions are called surgical emergency as surgery is advisable in emergent situations like this for optimal recovery.</li>
									</ul>
								
